pr_title: GSoC Midterm Evaluation: Steam Workshop SDK/Third Party Integration
pr_body:
- This PR is only for review and not for merging. You can view the second part here #2350 

Closes #1881. This PR is part of the ``Google Summer of Code 2023`` program.

I will be updating my Logs inside [my domain](https://k0t0z.github.io).

#### Note: :heavy_check_mark: means that SOG/unit tests for the corresponding function are provided.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Steps To Run The Code In This PR (Ubuntu Linux 64-bit Only) (``Working perfectly``):

```
Note: You may have to edit paths provided in the below steps depending on where you cloned enigma-dev
```

1. Download [Steam](https://store.steampowered.com/about/download).
2. Now edit the ``.bashrc`` and add these two important exports:
```
cd ~
```
```
vim .bashrc
```
 - 64-bit
```
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=~/Desktop/enigma-dev/ENIGMAsystem/SHELL/Universal_System/Extensions/Steamworks/gameclient/steambinder/Steamv157/sdk/redistributable_bin/linux64:${LD_LIBRARY_PATH}

export LD_PRELOAD=~/.local/share/Steam/ubuntu12_64/gameoverlayrenderer.so:${LD_PRELOAD}
```
 - 32-bit
```
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=~/Desktop/enigma-dev/ENIGMAsystem/SHELL/Universal_System/Extensions/Steamworks/gameclient/steambinder/Steamv157/sdk/redistributable_bin/linux32:${LD_LIBRARY_PATH}

export LD_PRELOAD=~/.local/share/Steam/ubuntu12_32/gameoverlayrenderer.so:${LD_PRELOAD}
```
3. Now run:
```
cd enigma-dev
```
```
./emake -r CommandLine/testing/SimpleTests/steam_general.sog -e "DataStructures,GTest,Json,Steamworks" -o /tmp/test
```

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Steps To Run The Code In This PR (Windows 64-bit Only) (``Working perfectly``):

```
Note: Windows support will be postponed due to an ABI issue as ENIGMA doesn't support MSVC yet, I recommend using Ubuntu Linux - 20/06/2023 00:45
```
```
Note: You may have to edit paths provided in the below steps depending on where you cloned enigma-dev
```

1. Download [Steam](https://store.steampowered.com/about/download) (I'm using v2.10.91.91).
2. Copy the ``steam_api64.dll`` from ``enigma-dev\ENIGMAsystem\SHELL\Universal_System\Extensions\Steamworks\gameclient\steambinder\Steamv157\sdk\redistributable_bin\win64`` (this is for 64-bit Windows so choose the one for your version) and then paste it into ``msys64\tmp`` directory. This must be done as LGM exports the executable in that location and we need that DLL to be with the executable.
3. Now run:
```
cd enigma-dev
```
```
./emake.exe -r CommandLine/testing/SimpleTests/steam_general.sog -e "DataStructures,GTest,Json,Steamworks" -o /tmp/test.exe
```

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Steps To Run The Example (Ubuntu Linux 64-bit Only) (``Working perfectly``):

```
Note: You may have to edit paths provided in the below steps depending on where you cloned enigma-dev
```
1. As Windows above but before running LGM, you must edit the ``.bashrc`` and add the two important exports mentioned above in the Linux section.
2. Now open LGM and hit the run button
```
java -jar lateralgm.jar
```

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Steps To Run The Example (Windows 64-bit Only) (``Currently crashes``):

```
Note: Windows support will be postponed due to an ABI issue as ENIGMA doesn't support MSVC yet, I recommend using Ubuntu Linux - 20/06/2023 00:45
```
```
Note: You may have to edit paths provided in the below steps depending on where you cloned enigma-dev
```
1. Currently Steamworks and Json extensions are enabled by default in ``steam-sdk-integration`` branch so you need only Steam to be running. Don't forget to log in with your Steam account.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Important Changes To My Plan:

 - The final output of the project won't be a C++ wrapper for Steam SDK as declaimed in my proposal. A layer between Steamworks ENIGMA's extension and Steamworks API will be created instead.
 - Project structure has entirely changed.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Done Before Coding Period:

 - Started Implementing C++ wrapper.
 - Started Implementing [General API](https://github.com/YoYoGames/GMEXT-Steamworks/wiki/General).

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## User Functions Progress (EDL Scripts Implemented):

:white_check_mark: [Management API](https://github.com/YoYoGames/GMEXT-Steamworks/wiki/Management)

 - :white_check_mark: steam_download_friends_scores();
 - :white_large_square: ``LeaderboardEntry`` data type
 - :white_check_mark: ``LeaderboardDisplayType`` constant
 - :white_check_mark: ``LeaderboardSortOrder`` constant

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Must Be Done Before Merging:

:white_check_mark: Adding support for other platforms in the Makefile file.
:white_check_mark: Switching the ``Default`` property in the Steamworks & Json extensions YAML file to ``false``.
:white_check_mark: Switching the ``cxxflags`` property in ``Compilers/Linux/gcc.ey`` to ``-fdiagnostics-color=always``.
:white_large_square: Reviewing all error messages and documentation in newly added files.
:white_check_mark: Adding the license to all newly added files.
:white_check_mark: Providing installation instructions for all platforms.
:white_check_mark: Modifying the extension to call ``steam_init();`` automatically when enabled.
:white_check_mark: Match all naming conventions with GMS's Steamworks extension.
:white_large_square: Testing the APIs with the latest version of Steamworks SDK, Steam, OS version, etc.
:white_large_square: Must test all EDL scripts in the example game provided.
:white_large_square: Providing SOG/unit tests for all functions written (this needs to be studied carefully as in order to test the C++ wrapper tester must have steam installed and running or I may use mocks).
:white_check_mark: Clearing garbage files.
:white_check_mark: ``DEBUG_MESSAGE()`` must exist only in APIs files. Try to remove it from wrapper files. Try to make the wrapper independent on ENIGMA.
:white_check_mark: Fix example game background design.
:white_large_square: Update the example game to match the latest version of [GMS Steamworks extension](https://marketplace.yoyogames.com/assets/10709/steamworks-ext).

:white_check_mark: The compiler must write a file next to the exe.
:white_large_square: Review includes.

:white_large_square: Commit the example game again and remove it from ``.gitignore`` file.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Differences With GMS:

1. ``steam_activate_overlay_user();`` function
 - GMS:
```c++
steam_activate_overlay_user(string dialog_name, int64 steamid);
```
 - ENIGMA
```c++
steam_activate_overlay_user(int dialog, int64 steamid);
```
```
dialog constants:
 - user_ov_steamid
 - user_ov_chat
 - user_ov_jointrade
 - user_ov_stats
 - user_ov_achievements
 - user_ov_friendadd
 - user_ov_friendremove
 - user_ov_friendrequestaccept
 - user_ov_friendrequestignore
```
2. steam_set_overlay_notification_inset();
 - GMS: Returns ``bool``
 - ENIGMA: Returns ``void``

3. The user can set the maximum leaderboard entries to fetch using the user variable: ``lb_max_entries``

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Troubleshooting:

1. If creating the ``steam_appid.txt`` file fails, just run the following commands for Linux:
```
cd /tmp
```
```
echo 480 > steam_appid.txt
```
For Windows:
Create a file ``steam_appid.txt`` and place it inside ``msys64\tmp`` directory. Don't forget to write ``480`` in that text file. IMPORTANT: This text file must be named ``steam_appid.txt`` and has ``480`` - which is the default App ID - inside it. Note: This file also must be placed with the executable.

2. On Linux, if there is something wrong with the exports, try to check the location of the lib using
```
find ~ -name gameoverlayrenderer.so
```

pr_review_comments: [{'comment_id': 1341873710, 'comment_body': 'I think @JoshDreamland will want you to delete this Steam logo.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 9, 30, 1, 2, 5, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'RobertBColton', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1341888448, 'comment_body': 'Done', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 9, 30, 3, 29, 14, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'k0T0z', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1341963494, 'comment_body': 'Feel free to replace it with an image that has just the word "Steam" or something.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 9, 30, 13, 41, 17, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'RobertBColton', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1342179576, 'comment_body': "@RobertBColton Actually, I think enigma can't detect SVG anyway so I need to create a new image.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 10, 1, 19, 42, 3, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'k0T0z', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1342194419, 'comment_body': "Correct, yeah, we don't have SVG support in the engine yet.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 10, 1, 22, 8, 33, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'RobertBColton', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1343381416, 'comment_body': "It'd be safer to use `std::unique_ptr` or other shared pointer types here if possible.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 10, 3, 2, 28, 1, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'RobertBColton', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1350219427, 'comment_body': '@JoshDreamland I think it will have unnecessary overhead. Using the ``new`` keyword is countable inside the Steamworks extension and I have already used smart pointers here but rolled it back as it injects unnecessary stuff and makes the code hard to read. If Robert still wants that change, I can make it happen Just review this comment, please.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 10, 9, 12, 6, 44, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'k0T0z', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1350220381, 'comment_body': '@RobertBColton Either way, after this, this PR is officially mergeable now.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 10, 9, 12, 7, 37, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'k0T0z', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1350222582, 'comment_body': "Also, regarding GMS's docs linking in the code, I will replace them after I write our documentation on the site.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 10, 9, 12, 9, 54, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'k0T0z', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_review_comments: [{'comment_id': 1341873710, 'comment_body': 'I think @JoshDreamland will want you to delete this Steam logo.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 9, 30, 1, 2, 5, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'RobertBColton', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1341888448, 'comment_body': 'Done', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 9, 30, 3, 29, 14, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'k0T0z', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1341963494, 'comment_body': 'Feel free to replace it with an image that has just the word "Steam" or something.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 9, 30, 13, 41, 17, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'RobertBColton', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1342179576, 'comment_body': "@RobertBColton Actually, I think enigma can't detect SVG anyway so I need to create a new image.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 10, 1, 19, 42, 3, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'k0T0z', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1342194419, 'comment_body': "Correct, yeah, we don't have SVG support in the engine yet.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 10, 1, 22, 8, 33, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'RobertBColton', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1343381416, 'comment_body': "It'd be safer to use `std::unique_ptr` or other shared pointer types here if possible.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 10, 3, 2, 28, 1, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'RobertBColton', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1350219427, 'comment_body': '@JoshDreamland I think it will have unnecessary overhead. Using the ``new`` keyword is countable inside the Steamworks extension and I have already used smart pointers here but rolled it back as it injects unnecessary stuff and makes the code hard to read. If Robert still wants that change, I can make it happen Just review this comment, please.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 10, 9, 12, 6, 44, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'k0T0z', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1350220381, 'comment_body': '@RobertBColton Either way, after this, this PR is officially mergeable now.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 10, 9, 12, 7, 37, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'k0T0z', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1350222582, 'comment_body': "Also, regarding GMS's docs linking in the code, I will replace them after I write our documentation on the site.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 10, 9, 12, 9, 54, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'k0T0z', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_title: Fix GTest extension build fails on installing it by building from source on windows
pr_body:
Fix #2338 

GTest extension must be installed using ``pacman -S mingw-w64-x86_64-gtest`` to be working correctly with the current ``ENIGMAsystem/SHELL/Universal_System/Extensions/GTest/Makefile``, but if you installed GTest with another way (building it from source and copy-paste files), it won't work because you will need the ``.dll`` file for linking it dynamically which is not provided when you build gtest from source, you only got ``.a`` files.

Using pacman or building from source gives you ``.a`` files, which you can link statically to your exe and this PR provides that change.
